@justinvp Interesting idea. One thing I have a hard time with is the relationship between `Workspace`, `Stack`, and `Config`. The example is missing a param for config:

```cs
var config = await ws.Config.GetAllAsync("bar");
await ws.Stacks.SelectAsync("foo");
await ws.Plugins.InstallAsync("aws", "2.0.0");
```

Both config and stack are keyed by stack name, which makes the grouping feel a bit odd. The config belongs to a stack and the relationship with workspace is only really for persistence. Not sure if this subgrouping over-emphasizes the relationship between config and workspace.

I am a fan of using better names for single value vs group operations on config.

