Each of those exceptions depend on the error descriptions included in `login_post_r.text`, which won't be sent by the new API. If an error occurs, the JSON object with the authentication response includes an attribute with the error description, `errorDescription`; none the sample errors descriptions included in the API documentation mention login failures due the lenth of the username, the password or for time out sessions, only a generic "Login Failed".

See page 8 of the current PACER Authentication API-Document:
https://pacer.uscourts.gov/sites/default/files/files/PACER%20Authentication%20API-Document.pdf

